(1) Grove Street, east side, north of Broadway, showing property of Loftus Wood at No. 16-18 (the house with the porch). This property which was badly damaged by fire on September 22, 1924, does not appear on the realty maps of 1929.

May 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, another view. Loftus Wood was president of the Franklin Ave. R.R. Co., now the Franklin Ave. Trolley line.

January 4, 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, another view. 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
